org.conqat.lib.commons.filesystem

Enum EByteOrderMark

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EByteOrderMark>
      • org.conqat.lib.commons.filesystem.EByteOrderMark
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<EByteOrderMark>

    public enum EByteOrderMark
extends java.lang.Enum<EByteOrderMark>
    Enumeration of the UTF byte-order marks (BOM). The actual values are taken from http://unicode.org/faq/utf_bom.html

    The order of the values in this enum is chosen such that BOMs that are a prefix of other BOMs are at the end, i.e. UTF-32 is before UTF-16. This way we can check the BOM prefix in the order of the enum values' appearance.

    Author:
    hummelb

      • determineBOM

        public static java.util.Optional<EByteOrderMark> determineBOM(byte[] data)
        This method checks the start of the provided data array to find a BOM. If a BOM is found, the corresponding enum value is returned. If possible, the provided data should at least be of size 4. Otherwise the encoding might not be detected correctly. However, the method also works with shorter arrays (e.g. if a file consists of only 3 bytes).

      • skipBOM

                                                  throws java.io.IOException
        This method determines which BOM, if any, the given stream starts with and skips it. The given InputStream must offer mark support.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
